<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="694" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.51/1752: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-08T12:00:00-03:00">March 8,
                                1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>96. My telegram No. 95, the Debt Service Decree was signed by the
                            President at 00:30 this morning. It will be released for publication
                            here and abroad tomorrow.</p>
                        <p>Department’s No. 58, March 7, 7 p.m., Aranha has changed his statement to
                            conform to the Department’s wishes.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>